==English==

===Etymology===
Prefix "neo-" (from greek 'neos'= "new") and "tropical" (from greek 'tropikos', referring to where the length of the day equals that of the night)

===Noun===
# Tropical America: the tropical areas of North, Central and South America. The tropics of "the new world". Used in biology, plural only.

